1277: The Condemnations of Étienne Tempier - Free Speech History|https://www.freespeechhistory.com/timeline/1277-the-paris-and-oxford-double-condemnation/|Rushd. In March 1277, the Parisian bishop Étienne Tempier issues a list of 219 forbidden propositions. The list includes the notion that “happiness is found in this life, and not in another”. The Archbishop of Canterbury issues the same list. Most of the condemned propositions revolve around the thoughts of Aristotle and Aristotelian philosophers like Thomas Aquinas, Siger of Brabant, Ibn Rushd (Averoës
